investigationEvent.text: A tall obese man in his 50s fell off his horse while jousting. Subsequent to the fall he had chronic back pain was registered in the German jousting association back pain registry. The patient had been self-medicated with 8 grams of paracetamol per day for 6 months when he developed life-threatening liver failure. He was hospitalised recovered with sequelae (persistent incapacity). A rechallenge was performed & the liver failure recurred. The reporter was certain that the paracetamol caused the failure
